Architecture plan for Issue #113

Module structure and file organization
- Keep the existing server-rendered admin page at `src/app/(admin)/admin/page.tsx` responsible for fetching posts, subspaces, and tags from Prisma and serializing those records for client components.
- Add a focused client component at `src/components/admin-content-tabs.tsx`.
  - This component will own only tab UI state and accessibility attributes.
  - It will receive the same data currently passed directly to `PostEditorPanel`, `SubspaceAdminPanel`, and `TagAdminPanel`.
  - It will render the three existing panels without changing their internal state, API helpers, or backend endpoints.
- Update `src/app/(admin)/admin/page.tsx` to import `AdminContentTabs` and replace the three stacked management `<section>` blocks with one tabbed content area.
- No database, Prisma schema, Rust API, auth, storage, or public page changes are needed.

Shared types
- Reuse existing exported admin API types from `src/lib/admin-api.ts`:
  - `SerializedPost`
  - `SerializedSubspace`
  - `SerializedTag`
- The new component props should keep these exact types to avoid duplicating data contracts.

Dependencies
- This issue depends on the existing `PostEditorPanel`, `SubspaceAdminPanel`, and `TagAdminPanel` components already being present and functional.
- There are no cross-issue dependencies in this batch and no migration requirements.

Key design decisions
- Default active tab is `Posts` so the existing admin post creation flow remains visible by default and current E2E assumptions continue to hold.
- Use semantic ARIA tabs:
  - container with `role="tablist"`
  - each tab button with `role="tab"`, `aria-selected`, `aria-controls`, and stable IDs
  - each panel with `role="tabpanel"`, `aria-labelledby`, and hidden state for inactive panels
- Keep all panels mounted only as needed by the active tab unless tests reveal state preservation is required. If preserving in-progress edits between tabs matters, keep all panels mounted and hide inactive panels with `hidden`.
- Preserve existing panel labels and visual styling by wrapping each panel in the same bordered panel style currently used on the admin page.
- Do not alter authentication behavior; `/admin` stays protected by the existing admin/session flow.

Verification plan
- Run TypeScript checks after implementation.
- Run or update the relevant admin E2E flow if available, ensuring the Posts tab is active by default and Subspaces/Tags tabs can be selected.
